	<article>

		<header>
			
			<h1>Road map for ESA-EU negotiations</h1>

			
			<h4>
												14 September 2004
										</h4>

					</header>


				<div class="intro">

						<p> The joint 'road map’ agreed at the opening of the ESA-EU EPA negotiations in Mauritius in February 2004 reiterated the overall objectives agreed during the first, all-ACP, phase of the negotiations.</p>

		</div>
		
		
					<p> It was agreed that negotiations would be carried out on two levels: ministerial and ambassadorial/senior officials. It was agreed that each side should organise itself according to its own internal structures. The joint negotiations will be divided into three phases: p&gt; </p>
<ul>

<li>I Setting priorities (March-August 2004); </li>

<li>II Substantive negotiations (September 2004-December 2005); </li>

<li>III Continuation and finalisation (January 2006-December 2007). </li>

</ul>
<p> Phase I will establish the general framework for negotiations and a tentative list of priorities for negotiations. Phase II will involve substantive negotiations on all issues relevant to EPAs and will be prepared by ambassadors and senior officials in July 2004. Phase III will see substantive negotiations continued to a conclusion, with disagreements being ironed out and compromises reached. Each party will use this phase to enact necessary legislation for the new EPAs to enter into force on January 1 st 2008 .</p><p> Negotiations will take place alternately in Brussels and the ESA region.</p><p> The ESA grouping will prepare the EPA negotiations around six themes: development issues; market access; agriculture; fisheries; trade in services; trade-related areas. Six ambassadors and six ministers and alternates for both have been designated to lead the discussions in the different groups as in the following table:</p><table class="renderedtable" border="1" cellpadding="2" cellspacing="0">
<tr>
<td width="168" valign="top">   <b>Issue </b> 
  </td><td width="156" valign="top">   <b>Ministerial lead spokespersons </b> 
  </td><td width="192" valign="top">   <b>Ministerial alternate spokespersons </b> 
  </td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td width="168" valign="top">   Development Issues
  </td><td width="156" valign="top">   Sudan
  </td><td width="192" valign="top">   DR Congo
  </td>
</tr>

<tr>
